item.dc:creator: @TehBawz TehBawz
item.description:
@TehBawz wrote:

you didn’t port-forward right or something, wrong with your IP. I could help you on skype if you’d like. I’ve had the same problem before.

Edit: “This happened to me when i first started out. If you Press
[CTRL] [ALT] [DEL] and open task manager, open up process tab.
You have a program that is running the port 43594, thus closing it off for your server. The most general one is uTorrent… If you have limewire utorrent itunes, anything close them all out then recheck the port.” Try this on your own first. then hit me up.
